721118f-a.text:
Lexington Avenue, west side, south from East 125th to 124th Street's. McClatchey's Bank Hotel is the two story corner structure which bears No. 134 East 125th Street. Adjoining same is the Harlem Savings Bank. To the left appears the branch office of the Provident Loan Society. This is at the N. W. corner
of East 124th Street.
August 1911

715307f-a.text:
167177 East 124th Street, north side, between Lexington and Third Aves. Building shown, is the old Kopper's Residence, built by Herman
Raub, said to be the oldest house in Harlem.
About 1920.
Wurts Bros.
